@lizzielucychapman has been consistently driving the adoption of digital finance and championing the concept. She founded @zestmoney which was selected as a 2020 Technology Pioneer by the World Economic Forum.

She currently serves on the boards of @indiamart (which is India's Alibaba) and IndiaQuotient (an early-stage investment fund).
She recently bagged the top honours in the Woman Ahead category of the Economic Times Startup Awards 2021. 

Lizzie is an energy ball of ideas and a force to be reckoned with in the world of fintech. 

On this episode of #WomenOnTopInIndia we talk about her move from finance to hospitality and back to finance, the future of the Indian fintech ecosystem, her tips for entrepreneurs looking to raise investment for the first time and much more. 

This season is powered by @ladieswlead which is a community for women professionals and entrepreneurs. If you’re interested to know more about the network and becoming member, please drop a DM to them. 

#womenentrepreneurs #ladieswholead #zestmoney #lizziechapman #gauridevidayal #womenontopinindia #podcast

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I was invited to be part of a very interesting and timely conversation about the future of plant based meats - is it a slam dunk for these companies or do they still have a long way to go? Tune in to @goodfoodinstituteindia ‘s Smart Protein Summit to know more. 

Posted @withregram • @goodfoodinstituteindia People have been saying we should eat chickpeas not chicken and broccoli not beef for decades, because of the things we all care about - climate change, greenhouse gases, ocean dead zones, deforestation, pandemics. 

But in the face of rising demand for animal protein over the next decades, we need to find more effective solutions. Smart protein can be that solution, because it's focused on giving people what they want. Guilt-free, delicious meat, egg, and dairy foods, but made from plants, cells, and micro-organisms like fungi rather than from animal slaughter. Foods which taste the same as the dishes we know and love, but are vastly better for planetary and public health? That's smart protein.

This is a glimpse of just some of the delectable plant-based meats that are going to market all over the country from companies like @bluetribeofficial, @imaginemeats, @shakaharryind, and @greenestfoods - punctuated by key insights from some of India's most well-respected minds in food: @gauridevidayal (@thetable_colaba @magstreetcafe @magstreetkitchen) & Keyur Bhatia in conversation with @varoonfive, MD, The Good Food Institute India.

Join us next week to watch more, learn more, and save your spot at the *essential* Summit on smart protein: www.smartproteinsummit.com!

🎥 @sjfernan

latestIgtvVideos.title: This Round Is On Me
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
The last few months have taught me one thing for sure - there really is no time like the present.
.
I’ve been thinking of doing a new podcast show for some time now (my last show is The Colaba Cartel also with @ivmpodcasts ). The obvious thing was for me to do something in the F&B space, but I wasn’t entirely convinced. Then the world went into lockdown and overnight, there was so much uncertainty in our minds, so many questions, not knowing how to navigate the way ahead. Our world was being flooded with Instagram lives and webinars but there was space for something with a bit more longevity and focus. I also realised that my potential guests would also be more likely to have time to spare now. That’s when it struck me that if I didn’t do it now, I never would. 
.
Welcome to Episode 0 of This Round Is On Me. An insightful show which focuses on global topics and trends emerging post the pandemic and deep dives into them with industry Thought Leaders and Experts. The show aims to inspire and challenge you, and perhaps help you rewire your approach going forward. Episodes will drop every Wednesday beginning 2nd September - you can tune in on the @ivmpodcasts website or app or wherever you usually get your podcasts from.
.
A huge thanks to @kavitarajwade @thestorybrewers and team @ivmpodcasts for handholding me through this, @jayyousuf and Dia for giving me space and the occasional quiet during recording time, @matchstick_graphic for a logo I love and ofcourse to all the über cool guests who’ve taken a chance on me and given me their valuable time.
.
So join me every Wednesday, with your favourite drink, because this round is on me.
.
#podcast #thisroundisonme #ivmpodcasts #newshow #podcastersofinstagram #podcastlife

latestPosts.caption:
We did it, again! 🏆

The Table is on the list of Asia’s 50 Best Restaurants 2025, ranking at No. 88!

Between all the risks we’ve taken and the endless pursuit of something better, this recognition is a reminder that trusting our instincts pays off. The Table has always been about evolution — pushing boundaries while staying true to what makes dining here special. Making it to the Asia’s 50 Best list yet again feels like a nod to that journey, and we couldn’t be prouder.

To our team — who pour their hearts into every dish, service, and detail — this is yours. To our guests — who have walked through our doors, dined at our tables, and championed us through the years—this is because of you.

Honoured to be in the company of those who inspire us — thank you @theworlds50best, our peers, purveyors, and everyone who’s been part of this journey.

Here’s to the pursuit of something special, always. #Asias50Best #TheTableColaba

If one more person tells me they’re going to Hong Kong this summer, I’m literally getting on the flight with them. 

Missing that city’s crazy energy, killer food and my favourite bar in the world. 

@jayyousuf feel free to surprise me with a long weekend 😆

Flashback courtesy @soulcompanyindia  @discoverhongkong #discoverhongkong #hongkong

To be honest, when @somannapm signed me up for the vegetarian only day of @auronithologist 2 night pop up in Ahmedabad last weekend, I was a little bit disappointed, being the hardcore carnivore that I am. 

But from the subtle flavours of karela in the tofu salad, to the momos in Rizala gravy that were deceptively meaty and the onion-poppy seed batta that accompanied the perfectly comforting khichdi, this meal was a hit in my books. A true sign of success is that I didn’t miss non veg even for a minute. Chef Auroni blew me away with his cooking. 

I’m going to take a wee bit of credit for pushing him to do a veg tasting menu the first time he came to @magazinestkitchen when he wanted to showcase non veg only and I told him he would be missing out on a large section of the Bombay audience - he’s clearly been killing it ever since. 

Good luck Chef, for all the exciting adventures and new beginnings to come this year. 

PS. Icing on the mishti was a reunion with chef Milon who was part of the opening team at The Table. Always a joy to see him acing it in the kitchen. 

Also, @amit_ia can you pls recreate @blockheads.india in Bombay already?

#ahmedabad #chefauronimookerjee

How do you build a space that feels like it belongs to everyone? Ask everyone to build it with you.

When @akhilasrinivas began designing @conservatory.blr, she didn’t start with a blueprint, she started with a question. And then more questions. To the community.

Because for her, building a space was never just about bricks and beams. It was about listening, about belonging.

In the season finale, we trace the journey of the keeper of cool culture herself. From architect to cultural catalyst, and how she built @thecourtyardcommunity, @conservatory.blr, and @wineinprogressblr into some of Bengaluru’s most magnetic spaces where food, art, and community collide.

Tune in now via the link in bio! 🎧
